        "title": "Mana"
      },
      "slots": {
        "default": [
          {
            "id": "8b2d2a49-a086-4b3b-8a07-7a670c3b89e3",
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {
              "text": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Mana came directly from Glooey. It created lots of it. Then used it to\ncreate the Tools. They then created everything. Glooey added a little\n\"oomph\" in the mix, to destabilize symmetry and make interesting things\nhappen.There is nothing mana can't do.maximum manamana regenerationmana\ncostpresent in every living creaturealso present in\nobjectsMagicaptitudehas to be\nlearnedhttps://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MusclesAreMeaningless",
                  "marks": []
                }
              ]
            },
            "slots": {}
          },
          {
            "id": "fcb028fb-f520-4fce-9ce2-439a0894dbed",
            "type": "paragraph",
            "attrs": {
              "text": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ""
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Mana is like dark energy/the forceit permeates the entire universe, and\ncan be concentrated within objects, living beings, locations, etcwhile\nit is generally \"everywhere\", it is not uniformly distributed. the\n\"main\" planet of our story happens to be a place with particularly high\nconcentration.Magic is the \"burning\"/manipulation (should it be\nconsumed?) of mana to release energy, which can be used for various\nprocesses.Upon being consumed through the use of magic, beings and\nobjects can slowly replenish their depleted reserves.all mana in the\nuniverse was created during the emergence, and in time will inevitably\nbe depleted as it gets used as magical fuel.Living beings can accumulate\nstores of mana inside them, serving as a stockpile for later use. Once\nconsumed, these stores can slowly replenish by the passive absorption of\nmana from the environment, much like osmosis. The total amount a being\ncan store, as well as how fast they can replenish their reserves can be\nimproved with training.how much mana a being has stored usually\ncorresponds to how powerful they areTypes of MagicRunesSpellsthe actual\nabilities characters and creatures use, usually\nnamedEnchantments\"Chakrasmithing\"/forgingAgingImbuingSealing (could also\nseal creatures like priston crystals, or naruto summons etc,\nspirits)blood/lifeforceCrystalsmana concentrates on them, and their\ncrystallized formations can be used to channel and amplify magic through\nthemelderelder magic is the only strong enough to actually create or\ndestroy things. everything else merely manipulates it. it is found only\non glooey and on the elder tools",
                  "marks": []
                }
              ]
            },
            "slots": {}
